RACE.RACE_TEXT: REMINGTON PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 98. Starter Allowance Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 14, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since August 14, 2023 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (If management deems it necessary to take this race off the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWENTYONE N CHANGE showed good early speed and dueled for the lead while two wide on the turn, was in a hard drive then bore out and bumped with QUARKEY inside the furlong marker twice then held on in the strides. SATURDAY'S GOLD was pinched back at the start then settled, rallied five wide in upper stretch and closed extremely fast on the outside and just missed in a game effort. QUARKY chased the early pace while two wide into the turn, rallied and was three wide for the stretch drive, was bumped twice by TWENTYONE N CHANGE inside the furlong marker and forced out then hung in the final strides. IAN GLASS was angled inside to saved ground on the turn, made a bid two wide in the stretch but was no menace in late stretch. ATRAS dueled for the lead from the inside, was in a long drive but gave way in the stretch drive. TIN BADGE chased the early pace while three wide into the turn then failed to menace in the stretch. SAY IT NICELY showed brief speed while inside then dropped back on the turn. HACKER was unhurried early and was no factor. CAPT. ST. JACQUES was unhurried early while inside and was no threat. UPTOWN SOCIAL showed brief speed then stopped. A steward's inquiry was held concerning the stretch run. After reviewing the film's, the steward's disqualified TWENTYONE N CHANGE from first and was placed third for interference in late stretch. PER RULING FROM HIWU, SATURDAY'S GOLD WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR POSITIVE TEST.
